article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 85, IUPUI 71
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Reggie Hamilton scored 28 points and hit 7 of 8 3-pointers to lead Oakland, Mich., to an 85-71 victory over IUPUI on Thursday night. Travis Bader added 18 points, including 5 of 8 3-pointers, and Drew Valentine had 10 points and a game-high nine rebounds for the Golden Grizzlies (10-8, 5-0 Summit). Keith Benson blocked five shots. Leroy Nobles and Alex Young scored 18 points each to lead the Jaguars (8-9, 2-2), whose three-game winning streak ended. Stephen Thomas added 14. Oakland shot 51.8 percent (29 of 56) and was even better from 3-point range, sinking 65.2 percent (15 of 23). The Grizzlies also outrebounded the Jaguars 39-31. Oakland's largest lead was 50-29 with 1:00 left in the first half. The Golden Grizzlies are 29-1 over their last 30 Summit League games and have won 23 straight league home games.
